The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 20 October is 647,025 (1,149.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 16 October, there were 95,595 new confirmed cases (169.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 09 October, there were 91,218 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 5% ( 4,377 extra cases).
